  "prompt": "What are some good science documentaries, other than Stephen Hawking's Grand Design?",
  "response": "There are many excellent science documentaries that explore various aspects of the universe, nature, and technology. Here are some recommendations across different categories:\n\n### Cosmology and Space\n1. **Cosmos: A Personal Voyage** (1980) by Carl Sagan\n   - A classic series that explores the history and future of science, the universe, and human life.\n\n2. **Cosmos: A Spacetime Odyssey** (2014) by Neil deGrasse Tyson\n   - A modern reboot of the classic series, covering a wide range of scientific topics with stunning visuals.\n\n3. **The Planets** (1999) by BBC\n   - A detailed look at the planets in our solar system.\n\n4. **How the Universe Works** by Discovery Channel\n   - A series that delves into the processes that shape the cosmos.\n\n### Physics and Technology\n1. **The Atom and You** (2012) by BBC\n   - Explores the fundamental building blocks of matter and their impact on our lives.\n\n2. **Particle Fever** (2013)\n   - A documentary about the Large Hadron Collider and the search for the Higgs boson.\n\n3. **Inside the Milky Way** (2010) by National Geographic\n   - Explores our home galaxy using state-of-the-art computer-generated imagery.\n\n### Biology and Nature\n1. **Planet Earth** (2006) by BBC\n   - A visually stunning series that showcases Earth's natural habitats and their wildlife.\n\n2. **Life** (2009) by BBC\n   - A follow-up to Planet Earth, focusing on the behaviors of various species.\n\n3. **Human Planet** (2011) by BBC\n   - Explores the relationship between humans and their natural environments across the globe.\n\n### Environment and Earth Science\n1. **Earth: The Power of the Planet** (2007) by BBC\n   - Hosted by Iain Stewart, this series examines the geological forces that shape our planet.\n\n2. **An Inconvenient Truth** (2006)\n   - A film by Al Gore that raises awareness about climate change.\n\n3. **Years of Living Dangerously** (2014) by National Geographic\n   - Celebrities explore the impact of climate change across the globe.\n\n### History of Science\n1. **The Ascent of Man** (1973) by Jacob Bronowski\n   - A classic series that traces the development of human society through its understanding of science.\n\n2. **Connections** (1978) by James Burke\n   - Explores the intricate web of inventions and events that have shaped our world.\n\nThese documentaries offer a wide range of topics and are a great starting point for exploring the fascinating world of science.",
